cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with activity detection in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new framework involving a multi-scale pyramidal architecture, which involves designing a two-branch multi-scale temporal feature hierarchy and appropriately fusing multi-scale feature maps. This suggests that the paper may also belong to categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves end-to-end training and single-pass inferencing, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning, suggesting that the paper may also belong to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
